#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:2
msgid "Reporting a Bug"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:4
msgid ""
"Whenever you find a bug in Symfony, we kindly ask you to report it. It "
"helps us make a better Symfony."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:9
msgid ""
"If you think you've found a security issue, please use the special "
":doc:`procedure <security>` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:12
msgid "Before submitting a bug:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:14
msgid ""
"Double-check the official :doc:`documentation </index>` to see if you're "
"not misusing the framework;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:17
msgid ""
"Ask for assistance on `Stack Overflow`_, on the #support channel of `the "
"Symfony Slack`_ or on the ``#symfony`` `IRC channel`_ if you're not sure "
"if your issue really is a bug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:21
msgid ""
"If your problem definitely looks like a bug, report it using the official"
" bug `tracker`_ and follow some basic rules:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:24
msgid "Use the title field to clearly describe the issue;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:26
msgid ""
"Describe the steps needed to reproduce the bug with short code examples "
"(providing a unit test that illustrates the bug is best);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:29
msgid ""
"If the bug you experienced is not simple or affects more than one layer, "
"providing a simple failing unit test may not be sufficient. In this case,"
" please :doc:`provide a reproducer </contributing/code/reproducer>`;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:33
msgid ""
"Give as much detail as possible about your environment (OS, PHP version, "
"Symfony version, enabled extensions, ...);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:36
msgid ""
"If you want to provide a stack trace you got on an HTML page, be sure to "
"provide the plain text version, which should appear at the bottom of the "
"page. *Do not* provide it as a screenshot, since search engines will not "
"be able to index the text inside them. Same goes for errors encountered "
"in a terminal, do not take a screenshot, but copy/paste the contents. If "
"the stack trace is long, consider enclosing it in a `<details> HTML "
"tag`_. **Be wary that stack traces may contain sensitive information, and"
" if it is the case, be sure to redact them prior to posting your stack "
"trace.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/code/bugs.rst:45
msgid "*(optional)* Attach a :doc:`patch <pull_requests>`."
msgstr ""

